  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> egg[s]</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>(salt prevents the egg from cracking) and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for exactly 5 min, then fill a bowl of<strong> very cold water</strong> (use the Gousto ice packs to chill the water!) and add the <strong>cooked egg[s]</strong> to the bowl to cool down quickly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1646735757949-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1646735757949-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1646735757949-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1646735757949-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1646735757949-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a  drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and set the tray[s] aside until later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1646735768062-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1646735768062-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1646735768062-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1646735768062-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1646735768062-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a sheet of <strong>baking paper</strong> to your chopping board and sprinkle over a very generous dusting of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>sausage meat</strong> (remove the paper if required!) to form 1 giant meatball per person, then flatten the giant meatball[s] into a circle (big enough to coat an egg) onto the floured baking paper until you have 1 sausage meat circle per person</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1646735778907-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1646735778907-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1646735778907-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1646735778907-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1646735778907-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the baking tray[s] with the chips in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p><p>While the chips are in the oven, peel the <strong>cooled egg[s]</strong></p><p>Add a <strong>peeled egg</strong> to the centre of each <strong>sausage meat circle</strong></p><p>Wrap the <strong>sausage meat</strong> around each egg and seal it tightly on all sides so that there aren't any gaps – this is your <strong>sausage-coated egg</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646735790120-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646735790120-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646735790120-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646735790120-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646735790120-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>curry powder</strong> to a plate and give it a good mix up – these are your <strong>spiced breadcrumbs</strong></p><p>Add a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> to a separate plate</p><p>Turn the<strong> sausage-coated egg[s]</strong> in the <strong>olive oil</strong>, shake off the excess, then add to the <strong>spiced breadcrumbs</strong> and press firmly until evenly coated all over – this is your<strong> breaded egg</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
